CSS Notes: 

CASCADING STYLE SHEETS:
ALWAYS TAKES SELECTOR THAT IS AT THE END. IT IS DESCENDING ORDER. 
TAKES THE LAST INPUT IT RECEIVES AS THE SELECTOR


CSS PROPERTIES

Selector {
	Property:  value;
}
https://css-tricks.com/
paletton.com

	color: red;
	text-align: center;
	border: 5px solid purple;

LINK CSS WITHIN HTML FILE IN HEADER TAG

	<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="style.css">


CSS SELECTORS


CSS Cheat Sheet

Reference:
*https://www.w3schools.com/cssref/css_selectors.asp
*https://css-tricks.com/almanac/

Cascading Style Sheets at the most basic level it indicates that the order of CSS rules matter. 


.class
#id
*
element
element, element
element element
element > element
element + element
:hover
:last-child
:first-child
!important (not recommended)


What seletors win out in the cascade depends on:
-Specificity
-Importance
-Source Order
